      How old was Picasso when he met Marie-Thérèse?
      Marie-Thérèse was Picasso's love and principal muse from the time he came upon her—she was 17, he was 45—outside the Galeries Lafayette department store, in Paris, in January 1927, until 1941.Apr 13, 2011

      Why is Picasso's portrait of Gertrude Stein such an important portrait?

      What does self-portrait facing death mean?
      Picasso's last self-portrait is titled, “Self-Portrait Facing Death.” Painted less than a year before his death in 1973, it depicts Picasso's bulging eyes and aged aura, with deep lines across his face. Several critics believe it represents Picasso's fear of his inevitable death.
